<br>
If grouping with evil is bad because it aids the evil dude (even though it aids us, maybe even aids us more since evil is being slain), then trading with evil should be forbidden, (except maybe in cases where the evil guy is making an extremely bad deal).  <br>
<br>
If because evil and good simply can’t stand each other, then trading should be right out.<br>
<br>
If the restriction is simply because evil can't be trusted not to ninja loot, backstab, or otherwise betray those in the group, then trading is ok since the trade window prevents fraud.  But, that rationale is much weaker, and would seem to allow grouping with evil that 'could be trusted' not to act dishonorably {and nothing says villains can't have certain aspects of honor}.<br>
<br>
The reason I ask is because it seems somewhat hypocritical to trade with evil, yet not group with them.  And, I wonder if any guilds have the gumption to actually refrain from trading with evil.<br>
<br>
Admittedly, I am not well versed in the lofty discussions of good and evil, and very well may be missing the point.  If so, I humbly ask for enlightenment.  Also, if this has been thoroughly hashed out before, then a pointer to the topic would be most appreciated.<br>
<br>
Thank you,<br>
 <p>- Komaru Krucified<BR>
Council of the Silver Griffons<BR>
Adoring sister of Eliezer of Erudin <BR>
Journeyman Enchanter of the 2nd Circle <BR>
