<br>
The rationale he gave?  If he destroys the weapon, it won't fall into the hands of the enemy.  If he takes it and sells it...even to another Good or Neutral, then there is always the possibility that it will be used to oppose good.<br>
<br>
Should Pure Goods sell to Evils?  In my opinion, no...but then, that's just my opinion. <p><p><font face="Arial" size="2"><b><font color="#800080">Tuppen Tangledroots
