<br>
Is it possible to justify trade between good and evil folk? Im sure it is, when you reduce such activities to individuals with individual agendas. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  But in general, it seems wrong that the two sides would engage in extensive trading. War is war, after all; when nations are at war, they dont trade with each other, although individuals may chose to step outside the conflict and do so.<br>
<br>
Im interested in seeing how other folk justify it. As a neutral with tendencies toward the light, I might trade with both sides, but would be more comfortable supplying or accepting gear from lightbringers, provided there was a balance between light and dark. If there was a serious imbalance, I would tend toward supplying the lesser of the sides.<br>
