<br>
Some quests on this server require you to do things that perhaps your character just wouldn't do. Maybe you don't want to kill faeries, because you are a decent and holy sort?<br>
<br>
Well, a &quot;trade&quot; with an evil who does kill the fae is one way around it. Perhaps you /duel and &quot;loot&quot; the faerie bits you need from his cold dead hands, while the stealthy evil rogue &quot;steals&quot; the item he needs (but doesn't want the faction hits for) during the distraction of battle. The game mechanic used is the trade window.<br>
<br>
I agree with the whole extensive trade between goods and evils being rather silly. I also have a smidgen of pity in my heart for people who find creative ways around some of the really idiotic quest designs in this game. So I guess I think it is rather jarring (in roleplay terms) in general, but some instances fit storylines well - kind of like cross-alignment grouping.<br>
<br>
